  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor[Central/Exp in Coordinating procurement activities/ quotation requests, price comparisons and negotiations, purchase order processing]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Manage procurement activities across all projects, including sourcing quotations, conducting price evaluations and negotiations, issuing purchase orders, and handling post-award documentation.</li>\n  <li>Support the development of site budgets for newly awarded projects to ensure alignment with allocated costs.</li>\n  <li>Source market pricing and quotations across all trades to update and maintain an accurate pricing database, ensuring Purchase Order (RPO) requests and future budgets remain within acceptable cost parameters.</li>\n  <li>Secure multiple quotations for comparison and review quotation exclusions to minimize risk of unforeseen additional costs.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and update trade award status reports in relation to the master programme, working closely with site teams.</li>\n  <li>Lead price and contract term negotiations prior to award confirmation.</li>\n  <li>Gather and update quotations to support pricing charts and cost data records.</li>\n  <li>Compile and analyze statistical data and reports for completed projects.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and verify site expenses and ensure proper documentation and justification for cost adjustments in relation to approved budgets.</li>\n  <li>Draft general correspondence and maintain accurate tracking of all documentation and reference numbers.</li>\n  <li>Foster teamwork by sharing information and collaborating with team members to meet departmental objectives and performance targets.</li>\n</ol>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
